Come on, come on, come on.

02:10.683 --> 02:12.773
Whoo! All right, let's show 'em.

02:19.753 --> 02:22.773
You are in the Marines now, son.

02:24.803 --> 02:26.903
Let's see it.

02:30.823 --> 02:33.772
Sharp shooter!

02:52.753 --> 02:54.773
Again.

03:05.386 --> 03:07.395
Marina?

03:09.466 --> 03:11.435
Marina!

03:16.416 --> 03:20.335
Oh-ho, Juney, it's...

03:27.356 --> 03:30.505
Oh, baby, it's okay.

03:30.506 --> 03:33.425
I'm... Daddy's coming, I'm...

03:33.426 --> 03:37.396
It's okay.

03:38.416 --> 03:40.355
Hmm.

03:46.436 --> 03:49.415
Mm. English. You are American now.

03:49.416 --> 03:50.455
Marina.

03:50.456 --> 03:51.455
Stand here.

03:51.456 --> 03:55.445
Okay.

03:55.446 --> 03:56.515
Why the papers?

03:56.516 --> 03:58.535
'Cause people will want to know.

03:58.536 --> 04:00.375
That I stand for something.

04:00.376 --> 04:03.336
You look ridiculous.

04:05.638 --> 04:07.637
Lee, what's a man like you

04:07.638 --> 04:09.587
going to do with a rifle like that?

04:09.588 --> 04:10.778
I am going to hunt fascists.

04:13.708 --> 04:15.787
Ready?

04:15.788 --> 04:16.808
Now.

04:32.708 --> 04:37.707
Hey, Bill. I want you to
watch them closely today.

04:37.708 --> 04:39.657
I wanna know everything that goes on

04:39.658 --> 04:41.617
between George and Lee, okay?

04:41.618 --> 04:43.697
Yeah. Yeah, no problem.

04:43.698 --> 04:45.667
I like being in this new apartment,

04:45.668 --> 04:48.637
right underneath them.
Makes things a lot easier.

04:48.638 --> 04:52.727
Hey. They still have no idea who we are.

04:52.728 --> 04:54.707
Let's keep it that way.

04:54.708 --> 04:55.707
All right.

04:55.708 --> 04:57.667
- Get me?
- Yeah.

04:57.668 --> 04:59.658
- See you later.
- See you later.

06:17.748 --> 06:19.628
Howdy, stranger.

06:27.618 --> 06:30.758
You know, they say,
"Smart is the new sexy."

06:32.698 --> 06:34.797
I don't know anyone who says that.

06:34.798 --> 06:38.778
Oh. Well... I say it.

06:43.818 --> 06:47.648
Don't worry. Everyone's gone.

06:48.818 --> 06:53.697
Do you know anything... more uplifting?

06:53.698 --> 06:54.817
Not really, I'm just learning.

06:54.818 --> 06:59.667
Oh. How about this?

06:59.668 --> 07:03.797
How could I
dance with another...

07:03.798 --> 07:05.737
Ooh

07:05.738 --> 07:10.667
When I saw you standing there?

07:10.668 --> 07:11.687
That's catchy.

07:11.688 --> 07:13.637
- Yeah.
- You make that up?

07:13.638 --> 07:15.627
Oh, yeah. Just me and my mates,

07:15.628 --> 07:17.627
John, Paul, George, and Ringo.

07:17.628 --> 07:18.717
Your mates?

07:18.718 --> 07:23.687
Umm, yeah,
my imaginary friends.

07:27.678 --> 07:29.677
You're so odd.

07:29.678 --> 07:30.797
Just crazy...

07:30.798 --> 07:32.628
about you.

07:44.638 --> 07:45.707
Mr. Amberson.

07:45.708 --> 07:47.627
Yeah.

07:47.628 --> 07:48.698
You have a moment?

07:54.698 --> 07:57.627
When you take on a
responsibility to teach,

07:57.628 --> 07:59.647
you also take on a responsibility

07:59.648 --> 08:00.727
to set an example.

08:00.728 --> 08:02.677
An example?

08:02.678 --> 08:04.807
Hell, it's harder for girls.

08:04.808 --> 08:07.787
Different rules, you know?

08:07.788 --> 08:09.797
I mean, just take a look around here.

08:09.798 --> 08:13.177
Every pair of eyes you see,
there's two pairs you can't see.

08:13.178 --> 08:15.088
And they're all watching you,

08:15.089 --> 08:18.158
judging you, deciding
if you're good or bad.

08:18.159 --> 08:21.988
Girls here, they all wanna grow
up to be just like Miss Dunhill,

08:21.989 --> 08:23.088
and that's a good thing,

08:23.089 --> 08:25.168
'cause she's important.

08:25.169 --> 08:27.969
She's a new kind of woman.

08:29.179 --> 08:31.008
You care about her?

08:31.009 --> 08:32.018
Yeah.

08:32.019 --> 08:34.087
Then put her first.

08:34.089 --> 08:36.188
Protect what's important in this life.

08:38.129 --> 08:42.129
Discretion is the better
part of valor, young man.

08:45.139 --> 08:46.138
Right.

08:46.139 --> 08:49.048
Jimla-doo.

08:49.049 --> 08:52.029
I need to talk to you about
your defense this year, son.

09:10.979 --> 09:13.068
I'm gonna do something, I swear.

09:13.069 --> 09:15.028
Someone has to.

09:15.029 --> 09:16.029
Make...

09:17.109 --> 09:20.118
Jake, drop that. Listen.

09:20.119 --> 09:21.148
You gotta listen to this.

09:21.149 --> 09:23.138
Here. Listen.

09:23.139 --> 09:27.038
The... the fabric of society
is being torn apart

09:27.039 --> 09:29.078
by people like General Walker.

09:29.079 --> 09:31.068
We have seen before, haven't we?

09:31.069 --> 09:33.188
Men of power, grabbing
whatever they want.

09:33.189 --> 09:35.128
Thank God they're speaking English.

09:35.129 --> 09:38.008
I'm gonna do something, I swear.

09:38.009 --> 09:39.978
Someone has to.

09:39.979 --> 09:42.138
Make... make a-a statement.

09:42.139 --> 09:43.968
You got a new rifle.

09:46.029 --> 09:47.958
Send a message.

09:47.959 --> 09:51.118
An action that cannot be ignored.

09:51.119 --> 09:55.188
I'm gonna. I tell ya, I've got it in me.

09:55.189 --> 09:58.128
You have courage.

09:58.129 --> 10:01.158
And I have some friends.

10:01.159 --> 10:03.958
Powerful friends who can...

10:03.959 --> 10:08.028
help you be the great man
you... you want to be.

10:08.029 --> 10:10.118
I'm happy to introduce you.

10:10.119 --> 10:13.968
Marina, don't slam...

10:13.969 --> 10:16.958
This... this changes everything.

10:16.959 --> 10:18.128
What do you mean?

10:18.129 --> 10:21.958
George just told Lee to
assassinate General Walker.

10:21.959 --> 10:24.178
And he said he'd introduce
him to his friends...

10:24.179 --> 10:27.018
at the CIA.

10:27.019 --> 10:29.138
George is a handler for Lee.

10:29.139 --> 10:32.028
George is the gun. Lee's the bullet.

10:32.029 --> 10:33.168
CIA's pulling the trigger.

10:33.169 --> 10:37.968
And Walker is a test run for Kennedy.

10:37.969 --> 10:39.118
But you said he misses Walker.

10:39.119 --> 10:40.988
Then why would the CIA
stick with the shooter

10:40.989 --> 10:42.168
that misses the target?

10:42.169 --> 10:44.078
I don't know, I don't know.

10:44.079 --> 10:46.988
Maybe Lee's part of the
conspiracy right now,

10:46.989 --> 10:48.138
and he messes up, they cut him loose,

10:48.139 --> 10:50.068
but he goes rogue on Kennedy.
I don't know.

10:50.069 --> 10:52.059
So... What do we do now?

10:54.784 --> 10:56.815
We got to follow them both, okay?

10:56.816 --> 10:58.568
You take Lee. I'll cover George.

10:58.569 --> 10:59.793
- No, you take Lee.
- No, no, no.

10:59.794 --> 11:00.953
- I'll take George.
- No, you take Lee.

11:00.954 --> 11:03.743
I don't want Lee. All he
ever does is read books.

11:03.744 --> 11:05.823
Then he'll be easy.

11:05.824 --> 11:07.824
Close it up, close it up, close it up.

11:07.825 --> 11:08.844
All right, all right, all right.

11:08.845 --> 11:11.775
Close it up! Come on!

11:18.825 --> 11:22.874
Oh, Miss Mimi.

11:22.875 --> 11:26.873
How long did you think you'd get
away with it, Mr. Amberson?

11:26.874 --> 11:28.805
Or should I call you Mr. Epping?

11:39.825 --> 11:41.815
Thank you.

11:46.785 --> 11:47.865
Oh.

11:49.845 --> 11:52.914
Bill, I respect your
interest in my visit,

11:52.915 --> 11:55.874
but I think this matter
is best handled privately

11:55.875 --> 11:57.955
between myself and your brother.

12:07.805 --> 12:11.784
So, um, how did you find me in Dallas?

12:11.785 --> 12:13.864
You're not hard to follow.

12:13.865 --> 12:17.744
We never received your
immunization records.

12:17.745 --> 12:20.884
State school board requires
those for employment.

12:20.885 --> 12:23.764
Yours don't exist.

12:23.765 --> 12:26.864
I investigated your degree and
found out it was issued by

12:26.865 --> 12:30.814
what generously might be
referred to as a "mill,"

12:30.815 --> 12:33.874
and a call to your last
known address in Kentucky

12:33.875 --> 12:37.764
revealed that you use the name
Epping when it suits you.

12:37.765 --> 12:39.895
Okay, all right, I got it.

12:42.785 --> 12:44.934
I haven't taken this to Mr. Simmons.

12:44.935 --> 12:48.834
I came to you because
I believe in trust.

12:48.835 --> 12:50.945
You wouldn't break our trust, would you?

12:57.925 --> 12:59.924
No.

12:59.925 --> 13:04.784
I wouldn't.

13:04.785 --> 13:07.944
You're right, I haven't
been telling the truth.

13:07.945 --> 13:10.835
Well, not all of it.

13:13.735 --> 13:18.744
My real name is Jake Epping.

13:18.745 --> 13:23.784
I was given the name Amberson

13:23.785 --> 13:25.884
by the FBI

13:25.885 --> 13:29.834
when I went into witness protection.

13:29.835 --> 13:31.754
Witness protection?

13:31.755 --> 13:36.844
Yes, in 1959, I turned
over state's evidence

13:36.845 --> 13:40.834
for a case against the Mafia.

13:40.835 --> 13:42.754
What is the Mafia?

13:42.755 --> 13:43.844
The Mafia.

13:43.845 --> 13:47.774
Italian-American organized
crime syndicate.

13:47.775 --> 13:48.925
What did you witness?

13:54.825 --> 13:56.745
Well...

13:58.745 --> 14:02.904
I had this friend, Fredo,

14:02.905 --> 14:06.864
and his brother Michael

14:06.865 --> 14:09.794
had him killed on a fishing trip

14:09.795 --> 14:11.874
in Lake Tahoe.

14:11.875 --> 14:13.844
In return for my testimony,

14:13.845 --> 14:15.964
the FBI gave me a new identity.

14:15.965 --> 14:18.924
They set me up in Jodie,

14:18.925 --> 14:21.804
a place nobody would ever look for me.

14:21.805 --> 14:24.964
And Bill and I just keep
this place as a backup.

14:24.965 --> 14:30.735
You know, just in case they
try to pull me back in.

14:34.825 --> 14:36.795
I see.

14:39.785 --> 14:42.934
If you were revealed to be
an imposter in the school,

14:42.935 --> 14:45.894
it would devastate this community.

14:45.895 --> 14:48.734
Yeah.

14:48.735 --> 14:50.834
I won't say anything about it.

14:50.835 --> 14:53.815
Thank you.

14:57.855 --> 15:00.755
It's wrong to conceal things
from those you care for.

15:03.845 --> 15:06.764
What... what are you saying?
I-I should tell Sadie?

15:06.765 --> 15:09.924
If I discovered this
about you, anyone can.

15:09.925 --> 15:12.914
When you refuse to tell people
the truth, Mr. Amberson,

15:12.915 --> 15:15.913
you deny them their dignity.

15:15.914 --> 15:20.854
And for some of us, dignity matters.

16:39.865 --> 16:41.924
Hi.

16:41.925 --> 16:43.895
Hi.

16:48.875 --> 16:50.825
Wanna dance?

16:53.775 --> 16:56.934
What's the occasion?

16:56.935 --> 17:00.924
It's Friday.

17:00.925 --> 17:03.775
Yeah, I saw that in the calendar.

17:11.835 --> 17:13.803
I don't wanna move too fast.

17:13.804 --> 17:16.964
Oh, no.

17:16.964 --> 17:20.874
I know, I-I...

17:20.875 --> 17:23.874
Maybe I overdid it, but, um,

17:23.875 --> 17:25.795
I've just been thinking...

17:27.905 --> 17:29.895
I care about you.

17:32.895 --> 17:35.894
Care about you too.

17:35.895 --> 17:39.854
And I realized that

17:39.855 --> 17:42.834
being with me may be
costing you something

17:42.835 --> 17:44.845
more than it should.

17:47.765 --> 17:50.764
People talk.

17:50.765 --> 17:53.823
So I thought,

17:53.824 --> 17:57.824
if we could just have a place,

17:57.825 --> 18:01.874
just a moment, where...

18:01.875 --> 18:05.734
we could be our real selves.

18:05.735 --> 18:07.844
How's that sound?

18:07.845 --> 18:09.824
A bit dramatic.

18:09.825 --> 18:10.944
Yeah.

18:10.945 --> 18:13.944
All I really want

18:13.945 --> 18:17.925
is just to be right here with you.

18:21.955 --> 18:26.814
But if this is all, you know, too much,

18:26.815 --> 18:30.834
I-I, um, I-I totally understand.

18:30.835 --> 18:34.873
I did bring that record
player all the way from home,

18:34.874 --> 18:36.954
and it's really heavy.

18:36.955 --> 18:39.794
And that is one of my favorite songs.

18:39.795 --> 18:43.894
I guess I just, um...

18:43.895 --> 18:46.824
I don't... know a lot about you.

18:46.825 --> 18:48.904
I just wanna get to know you.

18:48.905 --> 18:50.895
Like, what's your middle name?

18:53.905 --> 18:54.945
Laurel.

18:56.775 --> 18:58.904
Laurel.

18:58.905 --> 19:01.755
My middle name's George.

19:17.915 --> 19:19.834
Hey.

19:19.835 --> 19:22.873
Sorry, I didn't mean to bother you.

19:22.874 --> 19:25.794
I just... I found this.

19:25.795 --> 19:28.824
I seen your baby girl
with it a couple times.

19:28.825 --> 19:30.775
Thought she might be missing it.

19:31.905 --> 19:35.884
I'm Bill. From downstairs.

19:35.885 --> 19:37.944
Yes. Bill.

19:37.945 --> 19:39.854
I'm Marina.

19:39.855 --> 19:42.775
Real
nice to meet you, Marina.

19:44.795 --> 19:48.834
Thank you, Bill. For doll.

19:48.835 --> 19:51.825
June, she has... not so many.

20:07.895 --> 20:08.935
Hey.

20:16.945 --> 20:19.933
You look different when you sleep.

20:19.934 --> 20:21.914
What's wrong?

20:21.915 --> 20:25.814
Nothin'.

20:25.815 --> 20:28.794
Tell me.

20:28.795 --> 20:32.914
How come you never tell
stories about your life?

20:32.915 --> 20:37.944
About your family, about
you and Bill growing up.

20:37.945 --> 20:40.864
You want family stories, I
can give you family stories.

20:40.865 --> 20:42.855
That's not my point.

20:53.785 --> 20:57.744
You got something to hide?

20:57.745 --> 21:00.924
I don't wanna hide anything from you.

21:00.925 --> 21:02.834
Good.

21:02.835 --> 21:05.815
I want us to be honest with each other.

21:08.965 --> 21:11.825
I just don't know if I can be.

21:15.965 --> 21:20.884
Sometimes people hide things
inside because they're afraid...

21:20.885 --> 21:23.894
that if they share them with others...

21:23.895 --> 21:28.784
It's gonna ruin everything?

21:28.785 --> 21:33.934
Is that what you're afraid of?

21:33.935 --> 21:38.924
I feel like I'm an
imposter in my own life.

21:38.925 --> 21:42.834
Everyone thinks I'm one thing,

21:42.835 --> 21:47.904
but I'm something else.

21:47.905 --> 21:49.885
I don't wanna be that way.

21:52.915 --> 21:56.884
I wanna...

21:56.885 --> 21:58.955
wanna start things over right now.

22:01.865 --> 22:03.865
Here, with you, in this room.

22:05.735 --> 22:06.855
This is what I wanna build on.

22:09.865 --> 22:11.815
Never look back.

22:12.965 --> 22:14.885
Okay?

22:15.945 --> 22:17.795
Okay.

22:22.855 --> 22:25.764
All right, I'm gonna tell you something

22:25.765 --> 22:27.745
that's gonna sound really crazy.

22:34.965 --> 22:37.764
What?

22:37.765 --> 22:39.935
Was that envelope there
when we got here?

22:44.865 --> 22:45.945
I don't know.

23:01.745 --> 23:02.883
What's the matter?

23:02.884 --> 23:04.825
It's just the hotel bill.

23:06.805 --> 23:08.774
You know what, I...

23:08.775 --> 23:12.804
forgot I have to do something with Bill.

23:12.805 --> 23:13.914
We... we'd have to go.

23:13.915 --> 23:14.914
We're leaving?

23:14.915 --> 23:17.754
I'm really sorry.

23:17.755 --> 23:18.955
I'm sorry. We... we've just gotta go.

23:21.895 --> 23:24.884
- The CIA?
- Yes.

23:24.885 --> 23:26.784
We're getting close.

23:26.785 --> 23:28.814
This is them telling us to back off.

23:28.815 --> 23:30.913
If the CIA are worried about us,

23:30.914 --> 23:33.754
why don't they just kill
us with a blow dart

23:33.755 --> 23:35.814
- or rat poison or something?
- This is a specific message.

23:35.815 --> 23:37.754
They're saying not only
they're gonna ruin me,

23:37.755 --> 23:38.934
they're gonna ruin Sadie too.

23:38.935 --> 23:40.924
It's collateral damage.

23:40.925 --> 23:42.844
So break up with Sadie.

23:42.845 --> 23:44.854
- What?
- Break up with Sadie.

23:44.855 --> 23:46.824
Leave... leave Sadie out of this.

23:46.825 --> 23:48.814
I didn't get Sadie into this.

23:48.815 --> 23:50.784
All I'm saying is

23:50.785 --> 23:52.763
we gotta double down, all right?

23:52.764 --> 23:56.854
We need to clear up all this
shit with Lee and George. Now.

23:56.855 --> 23:58.824
- You wanna solve it?
- Yeah.

23:58.825 --> 24:00.744
Shoot Lee.

24:00.745 --> 24:01.944
I'm not convinced that it's Lee alone.

24:01.945 --> 24:03.954
But this says we're getting close.

24:03.955 --> 24:07.754
We're getting close to them,
and they don't like it.

24:07.755 --> 24:09.965
Just need to get a little bit more.

24:16.875 --> 24:19.824
George, I don't wanna do this.
Okay, let's just go home.

24:19.825 --> 24:21.804
Be quiet. If they sense something's up,

24:21.805 --> 24:23.744
they won't let us in.

24:23.745 --> 24:26.873
- Yes?
- Candy bar.

24:26.874 --> 24:28.795
- Come on in.
- Voilà.

24:29.865 --> 24:31.834
All right, look.

24:31.835 --> 24:33.734
George said that he was
gonna introduce Lee

24:33.735 --> 24:34.834
to his powerful friends.

24:34.835 --> 24:35.954
This might be the meet.

24:35.955 --> 24:37.774
I don't like this.

24:37.775 --> 24:38.794
- Just come on.
- At all!

24:38.795 --> 24:40.864
Come on, Bill.

24:40.865 --> 24:42.784
We've gotta get close
enough to hear them

24:42.785 --> 24:43.954
without them seeing us.

24:43.955 --> 24:48.813
Gotta hear the plan go
from the CIA to Lee.

24:48.814 --> 24:50.904
- Yes?
- Candy bar.

24:50.905 --> 24:52.774
Come on in.

24:52.775 --> 24:54.744
- All right.
- This isn't gonna work.

